article.description: — Xavier Fuller had 20 points as South Dakota edged past Southern 71-68 on Friday night.
article.headline: Fuller scores 20 to lead South Dakota past Southern 71-68
article.linkText: Fuller scores 20 to lead South Dakota past Southern 71-68
article.story: VERMILLION, S.D. -- — Xavier Fuller had 20 points as South Dakota edged past Southern 71-68 on Friday night. Fuller hit 9 of 11 from the free throw line. Erik Oliver had 11 points for South Dakota (2-1). Tasos Kamateros added 10 points. Mason Archambault had seven rebounds. Kruz Perrott-Hunt, who led the Coyotes in scoring heading into the matchup with 12.0 points per game, shot only 17% in the game (1 of 6). Jayden Saddler had 19 points for the Jaguars (1-3). P.J. Byrd added 13 points. Brion Whitley had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
